<p>Xiaomi has the right to modify this Agreement. Modified terms will be published on Xiaomi devices and the official website. Users can download and reinstall the Software or check the latest version of the terms of the Agreement on the website.  <strong>If you do not accept the modified version of this Agreement, you must stop using the services provided by Xiaomi Home. Your continued use of the Xiaomi Home software and services provided by Xiaomi shall be conclusively deemed an acceptance of all such modifications.</strong></p>
<h3>I. General Provisions</h3>
<p>1.1 This Agreement is a binding agreement between you (or "User"), Xiaomi, and our operational cooperators (hereinafter referred to as "Cooperator"), with respect to Xiaomi Home (hereinafter referred to as "Software"), including its download, installation, and usage, and related services provided by Xiaomi.</p>
<p>1.2 The Software and services are provided by Xiaomi for installation on (including but not limited to) smart mobile devices, to provide services such as device pairing and operating smart products.</p>
<p>1.3 The ownership and operation of the Software and its services belong entirely to Xiaomi.</p>
<h3>2. Software license scope</h3>
<p>2.1 Xiaomi grants you one individual, non-transferable, non-sublicensable, and non-exclusive license regarding this Software.</p>
<p>2.2 The User may install, use, display, and run the Software for non-commercial purposes on a single mobile terminal device. However, the User shall not install, use, or run the Software for the purpose of any commercial operation. The User shall not copy, alter, or modify any data stored within the Software, any data released to the memory of any terminal device during execution of the Software, or any data generated during the interaction between the client and the server during execution of the Software. The User shall not operate the Software through other software or create any derivative of the Software in any form, including but not limited to plug-ins, bots, or accessing the Software and related systems through unauthorized third party tools/services. If the User needs to sell, copy, or distribute this Software commercially, e.g., in the form of software pre-installation or bundling, written authorization and permission from Xiaomi must be obtained.</p>
<p>2.3 The User may not install the Software on other terminal devices (including but not limited to set-top boxes, game consoles, television sets, and DVD players) without express written permission from Xiaomi.</p>
<p>2.4 The User may create a copy of the Software which may only be used as a backup for necessary purposes. The backup copy must include all the copyright information contained in the original version.</p>
<p>2.5 Unless expressly authorized in this Agreement, Xiaomi does not authorize any other rights to the User. Whenever the need for previously unauthorized actions arises, written consent from Xiaomi must be obtained.</p>
<h3>3. Acquiring, installing, and updating the Software</h3>
<p>3.1 The User should use the designated website or designated method to download and install the Software. Be careful not to download the Software from undesignated websites, so as to prevent mobile devices from being infected by malicious programs that can destroy user data and acquire confidential user information.  <strong>If the User acquires the Software from a third party unauthorized by Xiaomi, or runs a different installation package with the same name, Xiaomi cannot guarantee that the Software will work normally and shall not bear any responsibility for any damage thereby caused to the User.</strong></p>
<p>3.2 The User must select the version of the Software that matches the requirements of their terminal device. Otherwise, the User shall be responsible for any software problems, equipment problems, or damage caused by the mismatch.</p>
<p>3.3 In order to improve user experience and the quality of the provided services, Xiaomi has the right to replace, modify, and upgrade the Software from time to time, as well as the right to charge you fees for the actions mentioned above with your prior consent. The Software will notify the User about updates by default. In some versions, the User may decide whether to use this feature or not. After the new version of the Software is released, Xiaomi does not guarantee that older versions of the software will continue to be functional.</p>
