<p>4.1 You may use this Software and related services in accordance with this Agreement, local laws, and regulations. You shall not undertake any of the following actions:</p>
<ul>
<li>4.1.1 Remove copyright information from the Software and its copies; modify, remove, or circumvent the technical measures set by the Software for the protection of intellectual property rights.</li>
<li>4.1.2 Reverse engineer the Software; decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive the source code of the Software.</li>
<li>4.1.3 Modify or forge parts of the Software such as commands or data; add, delete, or change the features or operating effects of the Software; operate or disseminate the software and methods used for the purposes described above, regardless of whether such acts are for commercial purposes.</li>
<li>4.1.4 Use this Software to undermine network security, including but not limited to the use of unauthorized data or access to unauthorized servers/accounts; delete, modify, or increase storage information in public networks or other people's operating systems without permission; probe, scan, or test the weaknesses of the Software's system or network or other actions that might disrupt network security; try to interfere with or destroy the normal operation of the Software's systems or websites; deliberately spread malware or viruses or bring other damage to network security; forge TCP/IP names fully or in part.</li>
<li>4.1.5 Sign in to or use the Software and services through any third-party compatible software or system not developed, authorized, or recognized by Xiaomi, or produce, publish, or disseminate the aforementioned tools.</li>
<li>4.1.6 Without the written consent of Xiaomi, conduct any of the following behaviors to the Software and the information in it, including but not limited to using, leasing, lending, copying, amending, linking, reprinting, compiling, and publishing, establishing a mirror website, and arbitrarily developing any relevant derivative products, works, services, plug-ins, tag-ons, compatibility or interconnection by virtue of the Software.</li>
<li>4.1.7 Use the Software to publish, transmit, spread, or store content that violates any laws and regulations of the place where you are located.</li>
<li>4.1.8 Use the Software to publish, transmit, spread, or store content that violates the intellectual property rights of others, discloses trade secrets, or violates other legitimate rights of third parties.</li>
<li>4.1.9 Use the Software to publish, spread, or promote advertisements and spam.</li>
<li>4.1.10 Use the Software or any other service provided by Xiaomi in any other illegal way, for any illegal purpose, or in any way inconsistent with the terms of this Agreement.</li>
</ul>
<p>4.2 Rules on information publication</p>
<ul>
<li>4.2.1 You may use the Software to publish information which reflects your original views and which contains your original data, text, usernames, images, photos, personal information, media files, links, etc.  <strong>You must ensure that you have the intellectual property rights for the information you upload, or that you have been legally authorized to do so, and you do not infringe upon any lawful interests of any third party during the use of this Software and its related services.</strong></li>
